======================================================================
WEIGHT DISTRIBUTION OF PALEY QR CODE
======================================================================

  P_7 code: [7, 3]
    8 codewords (3 free variables)
    Weight distribution:
      w=0: 1 codewords
      w=4: 7 codewords
    Minimum distance: d = 4
    => [7, 3, 4] code
    NOTE: This is the HAMMING [7,4,3] code!

  P_11 code: [11, 0]
    1 codewords (0 free variables)
    Weight distribution:
      w=0: 1 codewords
    Minimum distance: d = 0
    => [11, 0, 0] code

======================================================================
CONNECTION: QR CODE AND TOURNAMENT H(T)
======================================================================
  The Paley adjacency matrix A serves DUAL roles:
  1. As tournament: H(T) = # Hamiltonian paths (topological)
  2. As parity-check: C = ker(A mod 2) (algebraic)

  The Fourier decomposition of H decomposes along the SAME
  eigenspaces that give the QR code structure:
  - k=0 eigenspace: λ_0=m, contributes to H_0 (constant)
  - k∈QR eigenspaces: all have same |λ_k|, contribute to H_2
  - k∈NQR eigenspaces: same |λ_k|, different phase, H_4+ terms

  CONJECTURE: The weight enumerator of the QR code is related
  to the partition function Z(β) = Σ exp(β·H(T))
  via some transform (MacWilliams? Poisson summation?)


